Class NoKnownAllergy

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hl7.vmr.r2.ClinicalStatement
      • org.hl7.vmr.r2.ConditionBase
        • org.hl7.vmr.r2.AbstractDeniedCondition
          • org.hl7.vmr.r2.NoKnownAllergy

  • public class NoKnownAllergy
extends AbstractDeniedCondition
    Use this class to model 'No known allergies' or 'No known drug allergies', or more generally, no known allergy to a class of substances. Common denials of allergies or intolerances to a class of agents can be expressed as follows: - No known allergies --> NoKnownAllergy with a conditionCode stating 'No known allergies'. - No known drug allergies --> NoKnownAllergy with conditionCode stating 'No known drug allergies'. - No known food allergies --> NoKnownAllergy with conditionCode stating 'No known food allergies'.
